<section class="py-24 px-6 relative z-10 bg-white">
  <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-zinc-200 to-transparent"></div>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 group">
    <div class="md:col-span-5">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight leading-tight text-zinc-950 transition-transform duration-700 group-hover:translate-x-2">
        The Real Cost of the Wrong Tool
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="md:col-span-7 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed mt-1 md:mt-0 text-zinc-500 relative">
      <div class="absolute -left-6 top-0 w-1 h-full bg-gradient-to-b from-zinc-200 to-transparent rounded-full transform scale-y-0 group-hover:scale-y-100 transition-transform duration-700 origin-top"></div>
      <p class="transition-all duration-500 group-hover:text-zinc-700">
        Licensing fees are visible. The hidden costs of a poor-fit tool are not.
      </p>
      <p class="transition-all duration-500 delay-75 group-hover:text-zinc-700">
        When employees spend 20 minutes extracting data from a system that should surface it automatically — that time accumulates. When an approval process requires five emails because the tool doesn't support the right workflow — those delays compound. When adoption fails and teams revert to spreadsheets — the original investment is lost entirely.
      </p>
      <p class="transition-all duration-500 delay-150 group-hover:text-zinc-700 font-medium text-zinc-600">
        Custom software eliminates the gap between how your business works and how your software works. The upfront investment is offset by the removal of workarounds, the reduction in manual effort, and the increase in data reliability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
